00:30:33,560 --> 00:30:36,840
這個是我以前一個舊約老師

843
00:30:36,840 --> 00:30:39,000
他有一次寫過一個很重要的文章

844
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:40,960
就是講詩篇23篇怎麼去明白

845
00:30:40,960 --> 00:30:46,200
他講了究竟應該怎麼樣去明白詩篇

846
00:30:46,200 --> 00:30:47,520
我想他寫得很好

847
00:30:47,520 --> 00:30:48,760
我看這麼多東西裡面

848
00:30:48,760 --> 00:30:52,040
我覺得最有份量、最有幫助的就是這個

849
00:30:52,040 --> 00:30:54,600
所以我就用英文幫大家寫

850
00:30:54,600 --> 00:30:55,200
Amit 幫我讀

851
00:30:55,200 --> 00:30:56,400
然後我解釋一下

852
00:30:57,400 --> 00:31:04,680
The grammatical historical approach interprets the psalms in context of their original composition.

853
00:31:04,680 --> 00:31:13,680
Yet we do not receive the Psalter's 150 psalms as stand-alone texts in their original compositional context.

854
00:31:13,680 --> 00:31:18,400
They come to us in an expanding interpretive and canonical context.

855
00:31:18,400 --> 00:31:22,880
The individual psalms are part of a canonical collection, the Psalter,

856
00:31:22,880 --> 00:31:28,600
the final form of which is the result of a long editorial or redactional process

857
00:31:28,600 --> 00:31:33,240
that only reached its conclusion at some point in the post-exilic period.

858
00:31:33,240 --> 00:31:35,720
他在講你的詩篇150篇

859
00:31:35,720 --> 00:31:39,040
每一篇都有它獨立的作者和背景

860
00:31:39,040 --> 00:31:42,840
但是他最重要的那個人不是寫詩篇的人

861
00:31:42,840 --> 00:31:46,280
而是將那些詩篇去收集一起

862
00:31:46,280 --> 00:31:53,360
那個人是在一個秘魯回歸的情景去收集這個

863
00:31:53,360 --> 00:31:56,360
於是他為什麼要收集這150篇

864
00:31:56,360 --> 00:31:58,960
因為以色列人是超過150篇的詩篇

865
00:31:58,960 --> 00:32:02,200
為什麼要放這150篇在這裡

866
00:32:02,200 --> 00:32:06,640
然後他現在重新將那些詩篇重新定位

867
00:32:06,640 --> 00:32:09,120
OK,繼續,還有的

868
00:32:09,120 --> 00:32:14,720
In recent years, scholarly attention has focused on this redactional process

869
00:32:14,720 --> 00:32:19,320
and the role it plays in determining the meaning of individual psalms.

870
00:32:19,320 --> 00:32:24,520
Is the shape of the Psalter, the location and ordering of the various psalms,

871
00:32:24,520 --> 00:32:27,480
and especially the location of particular psalms

872
00:32:27,480 --> 00:32:29,720
at the beginning and end of the Psalter

873
00:32:29,720 --> 00:32:32,440
and at the seams between its five books

874
00:32:32,440 --> 00:32:34,640
merely an accident of history

875
00:32:34,640 --> 00:32:37,840
or is there an editorial intention behind the shape?

876
00:32:37,840 --> 00:32:38,760
不說太多了

877
00:32:38,760 --> 00:32:42,760
就是說以前很多人都是喜歡讀某一段的詩篇

878
00:32:42,760 --> 00:32:44,200
然後問一下它的背景

879
00:32:44,200 --> 00:32:45,440
但是現在的人不是這樣

880
00:32:45,440 --> 00:32:48,400
現在越來越多的學者在想

881
00:32:48,400 --> 00:32:52,680
究竟是誰將這150篇放在一起

882
00:32:52,680 --> 00:32:55,720
然後放在一起砌成這個詩集的人

883
00:32:55,720 --> 00:32:58,040
他背後有什麼神學的目的

884
00:32:58,040 --> 00:32:59,800
這個更重要過

885
00:32:59,800 --> 00:33:04,920
起初那個讚美詩是誰寫給誰的

886
00:33:04,920 --> 00:33:10,400
And if this shaping of the Psalter is intentional, at least to some degree,

887
00:33:10,400 --> 00:33:13,800
then what theological agenda guided these redactors

888
00:33:13,800 --> 00:33:15,400
as they did their work?

889
00:33:15,400 --> 00:33:17,280
And more specifically,

890
00:33:17,280 --> 00:33:22,080
did these redactors operate with an eschatological agenda?

891
00:33:22,080 --> 00:33:25,080
In other words, was the Psalter edited in such a way

892
00:33:25,080 --> 00:33:29,720
as to encourage readers to interpret its constituent psalms

893
00:33:29,720 --> 00:33:32,280
no longer simply as prayers and hymns

894
00:33:32,280 --> 00:33:35,120
rooted in the experience of ancient Israelites

895
00:33:35,120 --> 00:33:40,480
but as prophecies of events at the climax of Israel's history?

896
00:33:40,480 --> 00:33:43,840
那些神學的東西,那些英文都不是很好

897
00:33:43,840 --> 00:33:45,320
好像令你很難明白

898
00:33:45,320 --> 00:33:48,120
但是其實背後的意義是很簡單的

899
00:33:48,120 --> 00:33:49,360
簡單的就是說

900
00:33:49,360 --> 00:33:54,240
究竟收集150篇的編輯

901
00:33:54,240 --> 00:33:57,000
他最後他的神學理念是什麼呢?

902
00:33:57,000 --> 00:33:59,840
他們會發現這個人有一個神學理念

903
00:33:59,840 --> 00:34:02,000
就是他會將所有的東西

904
00:34:02,000 --> 00:34:04,560
去到末世的觀念

905
00:34:04,560 --> 00:34:06,080
eschatological agenda

906
00:34:06,080 --> 00:34:07,080
他將所有的東西

